VCoinciding with the 92nd birth anniversary of veena vidwan K.S.Narayanaswami, a couple of veena concerts were organised at Vylloppilly Samskriti Bhavan, Thiruvananthapuram.The concerts began with a &#8216;Sapta veena&#8217; recital led by Maya Varma and party. After a varnam in Abhogi, Maya Varma, a disciple of Ahalya Thamburatti and Valiyasala Lalitha,  played  &#8216;Vatapi Ganapathim Bhajeham&#8217; in Hamsadwani. Muthiah Bhagavathar&#8217;s &#8216;Himagiri thanaye&#8217;  in Sudhadhanyasi followed. Swati Tirunal&#8217;s &#8216;Gopalaka Pahimam&#8217; in Revagupti was warmly welcomed by listeners. Maya Varma was supported by her disciples Nisha Ponnu, Saranya B.Mangal, Lekshmi Priya, Sasikala, Soniya and Bhagyalekshmi.As thukkada, Maya  played a garland of kritis in Yamunakalyani, which included &#8216;Krishna Krishna Mukunda Janardana,&#8217; &#8216;Krishna Nee Begane Baro,&#8217; and a couple of her own compositions.She concluded the sapta veena recital with &#8216;Raghupati Raghava Raja Ram.&#8217; The accompanying artistes were Malayinkil Prasad on the mridangam, Trivandrum Rajesh on the ghatam and Uduppi Sreekanth on the ganjira.The sapta veena recital was followed by the recitals of  N.J.Nandini, a disciple of Dr.S.Bhagyalekshmi, and Murthy. &#8216;Yenthu mudho&#8217; in Bindumalini, a janya of Chakravakam, and &#8216;Muruga nin&#8217; in Behag stood out for their chaste rendition.The evening came to an end with the veena concert by  Prema Mallikarjun. Prema  began her short veena concert with a Tyagaraja composition &#8216;Yajnadhulu&#8217; in Jayamanohari, a janya of Kharaharapriya set to Adi talam. She followed it with a Dikshitar invocation &#8216;Gajananam yudham&#8217; in Chakravakam. Swati Tirunal&#8217;s &#8216;Saroruhasana jaye&#8217; in Pantuvarali saw fine exchanges between Prasad and Rajesh on the mridangam and the ghatam respectively. Prema concluded her veena recital with a Swati Tirunal tillana in Dhansree, and &#8216;Padmanabha pahi&#8217; in Hindolam.The programmes were organised by the the four-year-old Veena Sangeeth Sangh.
